# PlantUML - UML Diagrams

PlantUML is ideal for class diagrams, sequence diagrams, use cases, and more.

## Class Diagram

<<plantuml>>
@startuml
class User {
  -id: int
  -name: string
  -email: string
  +login()
  +logout()
}

class Product {
  -id: int
  -name: string
  -price: float
  +updatePrice()
}

class Order {
  -id: int
  -date: date
  -total: float
  +calculateTotal()
  +confirm()
}

User "1" -- "*" Order : places
Order "*" -- "*" Product : contains
@enduml
<<end>>

## Sequence Diagram

<<plantuml>>
@startuml
actor Customer
participant "Web System" as Web
participant "Backend API" as API
database "Database" as DB

Customer -> Web: Request product
Web -> API: GET /api/products/123
API -> DB: SELECT * FROM products WHERE id=123
DB --> API: Product data
API --> Web: JSON response
Web --> Customer: Display product
@enduml
<<end>>

