# Combining Advanced Elements

All elements working together:

<<info>>
**Complete Example**
This section demonstrates how to combine CodeGroups, PlantUML, Grids, and Columns in a single document.
<<end>>

::: grid

::: column
### System Architecture

<<plantuml>>
@startuml
component "Frontend" as FE
component "Backend" as BE
database "PostgreSQL" as DB

FE --> BE : REST API
BE --> DB : SQL
@enduml
<<end>>
:::

::: column
### Example Code

::::code-group
```typescript [TypeScript]
// TypeScript
interface Config {
  apiUrl: string;
  timeout: number;
}

const config: Config = {
  apiUrl: "https://api.example.com",
  timeout: 5000
};
```

```rust [Rust]
// Rust
struct Config {
    api_url: String,
    timeout: u32,
}

let config = Config {
    api_url: String::from("https://api.example.com"),
    timeout: 5000,
};
```
:::
:::

:::

